HEADWORD: Low-spirited
<hw>Low"-spir`it*ed</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Deficient in
animation and courage; dejected; depressed; dispirited; not
sprightly.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> depressed, dispirited, down(predicate), downcast,
downhearted, low.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> + <source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Low"-spir`it*ed*ness</wf>,
<pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

